# Example local config for video-transcriber-mcp.
# Copy to `.env` and fill in real values. `.env` is gitignored.
#
# These are read from the process environment. When configuring the MCP server
# in Claude Desktop / another client, set them in that client's `env` block.

# ---- yt-dlp cookies (optional) ---------------------------------------------
# Needed for: age-restricted videos, members-only videos, and YouTube's
# "Sign in to confirm you're not a bot" challenge.
#
# Option 1 (preferred on headless / Linux): point to a Netscape-format
# cookies file. Export it however you like — e.g. a browser extension — then:
#YT_DLP_COOKIES=/path/to/cookies.txt
#
# Option 2: read cookies straight from a logged-in local browser.
# Set to one of: chrome, brave, edge, firefox, safari, chromium, opera, vivaldi
# (ignored when YT_DLP_COOKIES above is set).
#YT_DLP_COOKIES_FROM_BROWSER=chrome

# ---- Remote whisper worker (optional) --------------------------------------
# Offload transcription to a remote HTTP worker (e.g. a GPU service). When set,
# audio bytes are POSTed there instead of running whisper.cpp locally. The
# endpoint must accept multipart {audio, model, language} and return JSON
# {transcript, segments:[{start_ms,end_ms,text}]}.
#REMOTE_WHISPER_URL=https://your-worker.example.com/transcribe

# ---- whisper.cpp binary (optional) -----------------------------------------
# Override the whisper.cpp CLI binary name/path. Defaults to `whisper-cli`
# (installed by `brew install whisper-cpp`). Set this if you built whisper.cpp
# yourself or it's named `main`.
#WHISPER_CPP_BINARY=/usr/local/bin/whisper-cli
